text: Brașovia Brașov was a football team from Brașov founded in 1914 and dissolved in 1937. ==History== In their short lifetime they played 6 times in Romanian Football Championship, but without notable performances. They won the Brașov Regional Championship four times and qualified for the Romanian Champions Final Tournament : 1922–23, 1923–24, 1924–25, 1929–30. In the new league format of Divizia A they played twice in : 1932–33, 1933–34. ==Achievements== *Divizia A Semi-final (1) : 1924–25 ==Bibliography== * ==References== Category:Football clubs in Brașov Category:Defunct football clubs in Romania Category:1914 establishments in Romania Category:Association football clubs established in 1914 Category:1937 disestablishments in Romania Category:Association football clubs disestablished in 1937
